					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 14th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>75 membranes, 262 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>553</height>
										<width>4623</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>75 membranes, with wooden rollers. Silk mantle. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Small surface abrasions, especially over folds, and delamination. </p>
									<p>Some pleats and cockling.  </p>
									<p>Minor water damage; small area of salt accretion and a few stains at edges. </p>
									<p>Slight worming at one join.
</p>
									<p>Mantle damaged and fragile. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="262" ruledLines="42" writtenLines="42">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point.</p>
									<p>Visible stitching. </p>
									<p>262 columns in total, one to five columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>The second דרש of Lev. 10:16 is not placed at the beginning of the line. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on בדהיק, the letter ח is occasionally arched.  </p>
									<p>Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>Special shapes of the letter  נ, פ and broken ו occur. </p>
									<p>The &quot;puncta extraordinaria&quot; placed on the words fixed by masorah, except Gen. 16:5. </p>
									<p>Wooden rollers (currently kept in a separate box). </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
